Class FileToUpload

java.lang.Object
  com.serena.dmclient.api.FileToUpload

public class FileToUpload
extends java.lang.Object

Class to collect all returned information about a file that was passed in to the upload/upload command.

scanDirectoryEx

public static java.util.List scanDirectoryEx(java.lang.String path,
                                             boolean recursive)
Scans the given directory for files using the given pattern within path. Also scans the corresponding metadata directory and collects the information It then compares those two lists of files and returns a list of FileToUpload objects containing information about the metadata and also about the difference between the local file and the corresponding metadata file.

Parameters:
path - Path of the directory that should be scanned. I.e. C:\temp
recursive - whether the directory should be scanned recursively
Returns:
List of FileToUpload objects

scanDirectory2

public static java.util.List scanDirectory2(java.lang.String path,
                                            boolean recursive,
                                            boolean enableAdd)
Scans the given directory for files using the given pattern within path. Also scans the corresponding metadata directory and collects the information It then compares those two lists of files and returns a list of FileToUpload objects containing information about the metadata and also about the difference between the local file and the corresponding metadata file.

Parameters:
path - Path of the directory that should be scanned. I.e. C:\temp
recursive - whether the directory should be scanned recursively
enableAdd - When false, only returns additions scheduled for delivery.
Returns:
List of FileToUpload objects

scanSingleFileEx

public static FileToUpload scanSingleFileEx(java.lang.String path)
Scans the given file's metadata and returns that information and the difference between file and metadata in the returned FileToUpload object. The FileToUpload object can then be passed in into the Project.upload() method.

Parameters:
path - Path of the file that should be scanned. I.e. C:\temp\data.dat
Returns:
FileToUpload object
